						<summary>

						<p>Round the pillar set up in the <hi rend="italic">chandana-maṇḍapa</hi> of Raṅganāthasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 15: 986 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that the members of the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Śrīraṅgam agreed to burn a lamp with one <hi rend="italic">uri</hi> of pure ghee and five <hi rend="italic">karai</hi> of the camphor, called <hi rend="italic">bhīmasēni,</hi> daily in front of God Tiruvaraṅgattu-perumāṉaḍigaḷ from the interest on 71 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold endowed by Śrīdharaṉ Kumaraṉ, a <hi rend="italic">Malaiyāḷaṉ</hi> of Iravimaṅgalam in Vaḷḷuva-nāḍu of Malai-nāḍu.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XXIV No. 12.</p>						

						</summary>
